snippet.title: Amber Heard Sued for 10 Million Dollars
snippet.description:
According to Page Six‚Äôs Oli Coleman, Amber Heard may come to wish that she hadn‚Äôt given away her divorce money from Johnny Depp to charity.

"The actress is being sued for $10 million for her part in an alleged conspiracy to sabotage the drama ‚ÄúLondon Fields,‚Äù according to the Hollywood Reporter.

The star-studded film features Heard as a psychic who foresees her own murder, alongside actors Billy Bob Thornton and Jim Sturgess, with a cameo by her former husband Johnny Depp.

In the suit, which was filed Monday in Los Angeles Superior Court, production company Nicola Six (named for Heard‚Äôs character in the movie) claims that Heard ‚Äî along with director Mathew Cullen ‚Äî breached her contract by refusing to shoot the agreed-upon script and failing to show up at the Toronto International Film Festival to promote the movie.

‚ÄúWhile the inherent tension between actors and directors and producers is nothing new in Hollywood, the unauthorized and unlawful acts of Heard, Cullen, and others ‚Äî most notably, their campaign to damage the Picture and the Picture‚Äôs investors ‚Äî are perhaps unprecedented.‚Äù

It goes on, ‚ÄúIndeed, as a result of their misconduct, which continues to this day, the very promising Picture remains in limbo, hijacked and placed under a cloud by Heard, Cullen, and others.‚Äù
It seems that the actress hoped to support Cullen, who has sued Nicola Six claiming that it had edited the movie ‚Äî an adaptation of the Martin Amis novel ‚Äî to include scenes of 9/11 ‚Äújumpers‚Äù cut with pornography, and hadn‚Äôt funded the movie in the way they had promised.

Nicola Six‚Äôs suit claims that, ‚ÄúIn an effort to intimidate Nicola Six, Heard falsely claimed to Nicola Six that she had not contractually agreed to allow the use of nudity in the Picture‚Äù and that she refused to act in ‚Äúprovocative scenes,‚Äù meaning that ‚Äúkey scenes in the script had to be removed and/or rewritten to accommodate Heard‚Äôs behavior.‚Äù

In August, Heard announced that she was donating her $7 million divorce settlement from Depp ‚Äî who also has a small role in the movie ‚Äî to the ACLU and the Children‚Äôs Hospital of Los Angeles after the couple‚Äôs acrimonious split."

http://pagesix.com/2016/11/21/amber-heard-is-being-sued-for-10-million/
